title: Assets under supervision at Goldman Sachs 2009 to 2018
yAxis: Assets under supervision in billion U.S. dollars
summary: The chart at hand is a line chart where the x axis denotes Year and a y axis denotes Assets under supervision in billion U.S. dollars. In total the number of data points it has is 10.
In general Assets under supervision in billion U.S. dollars has rose over the Year.
Assets under supervision in billion U.S. dollars is roughly constant from 2009 to 2011, gradually increasing from 2011 to 2016, and lastly roughly constant from 2016 to 2018.
The steepest increase occurs in between the Year 2013 and 2014.
The highest Assets under supervision in billion U.S. dollars, of value 1542.0 was reached at Year 2018
Minimum Assets under supervision in billion U.S. dollars about 871.0 was reached at Year 2009
